org.cougaar.core.blackboard
Interface MessageManager

public interface MessageManager

A message acknowledgement manager used by the Distributor's non-lazy persistence mode to ensure that unacknowledged messages are persisted.

Method Detail

start

void start(MessageSwitchService msgSwitch,
           boolean didRehydrate)
Start the message manager running. The message manager should be inactive until this method is called because it does know know the identity of the agent it is in.

stop

void stop()
Stop the message manager, halting any internal activity.

sendMessages

void sendMessages(java.util.Iterator messages)
Add a set of messages to the queue of messages waiting to be transmitted. When persistence is enabled, the messages are held until the end of the epoch.

receiveMessage

int receiveMessage(DirectiveMessage aMessage)
Incorporate a directive message into the message manager's state.

Returns:
Normally, the message is returned, but duplicate and from the future messages are ignored by returning null.

receiveAck

int receiveAck(org.cougaar.core.blackboard.AckDirectiveMessage theAck)
Incorporate a directive acknowledgement into the message manager's state. The acknowledged messages are removed from the retransmission queues.

acknowledgeMessages

void acknowledgeMessages(java.util.Iterator messagesToAck)
Prepare to acknowledge a list of directive messages. The acknowledgements are not actually sent until the end of the epoch.

advanceEpoch

void advanceEpoch()
Advance epoch. Bring the current epoch to an end in preparation for a persistence delta.

needAdvanceEpoch

boolean needAdvanceEpoch()
